'''Melo''' (also known as Malo) is an [[Afro-Asiatic languages|Afro-Asiatic]] language spoken in the [[Gamo Gofa Zone]] of the [[Southern Nations, Nationalities, and People's Region]] in [[Ethiopia]].<ref>Raymond G. Gordon Jr., ed. 2005. ''Ethnologue:  Languages of the World''. 15th edition. Dallas:  Summer Institute of Linguistics.</ref>

